        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><strong>Rust to Revitalization Act of 2022</strong></p> <p>This bill sets forth a special rule for the certification and designation of a population census tract as a qualified opportunity zone. The population census tract must have a population of zero, was previously used for industrial purposes and is a brownfield industrial site, and is contiguous, including by water, to a population census tract that has been designated as a qualified opportunity zone. </p> <p>A<em> qualified opportunity zone</em> is an economically distressed community where new investments, under certain conditions, may be eligible for preferential tax treatment.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
